The paper proposes a method for super-resolution of images using back-propagation neural networks and non-local means denoising. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with image processing and signal processing, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
